Visualisation of EuroMed Earthquakes from the INGV EuroSeismos project¶

http://storing.rm.ingv.it/es_web/ using python¶

Part I: This is a first summary of the earthquake data contained within the INGV database in order to first understand what is included in this database. After that we may perform some spatial analysis to further understand this dataset The earthquake data in this notebook have been downloaded from here: http://storing.rm.ingv.it/es_web/

Some of things we are showing here are the following:¶
  • Review content of INGV Euro - Mediterranean earthquakes dataset
  • Show how to read the csv file & show different ways to summarize the dataset
  • How to print few lines from a file in order to check contents
  • Sort and summarize data and plot it

Data Summary & Content¶

The datasets we are reading have been downloaded from the INGV website provided above, and provide a list of what kind of events we have per country and per year The reason behind this is to understand the content as-of-date of the INGV database as a repository of historical earthquakes for the European

Mediterranean region¶

# How do we plot now the aggregate data to make a bar graph?
# This resolves the issue
plt.rcParams["figure.figsize"] = (40,10)

d1 = qk1895_1930_df.groupby( ["Country"] ).size().reset_index(name='count')
x = d1['Country'] # what goes on the x-axis
y = d1['count']   # what goes on the y-axis

# naming the x axis
plt.xlabel('Country', fontsize=20)
# naming the y axis
plt.ylabel('Number of Earthquakes', fontsize=20)
plt.bar(x,y)
plt.xticks(rotation = 'vertical') # rotates x-axis labels for better viewing and fit
plt.title('Earthquakes from 1895 to 1930 per country', fontsize=30)

plt.xticks(fontsize=20)
plt.yticks(fontsize=20)

plt.grid(True)
plt.show()

map2 = folium.Map(location=[30, 38],
               tiles='openstreetmap',

    row=greek_quakes.iloc[i]
    lat,long=row.Lat,row.Lon
    folium.CircleMarker(
    location = [lat,long],
    radius = float(row.M/rowmax*10),
    popup = str(row['Da'])+"/"+str(row['Mo'])+"/"+str(row['Year'])+ " " +str(row["Epicentral_Zone"])+" " + str(row['Country'])
